texts.text: Here you go Lachesis, the thread is spun.
Here you go Atropos, the thread is measured.
There. The thread is cut, my sisters.
>High upon Mount Olympus,
>The Moirae sisters weave the threads of fate as always.
Deciding the fate of mortals really is dreary work, don't you think?
Indeed it is, my sister. Is there anything that can relieve the drudgery?
Would you like to listen to the wishes and hopes of humans?
I'm sure they are just trivial things as usual, but still...
Please let me win the draw for the next concert ticket...
O God, please let me qualify for the school I want to get into!
Please let me win the writing contest! Pleeeeease!
...You were right. They are trivial.
But wait, what have we here...?
Help... Somebody help... Hero...!
Did he say hero? Do the humans need a hero?
By hero does he mean the monster slaying kind?
We haven't had one of those in a long time, it would be nice to see those patterns again.
Hey everyone, you all here?
Yup, what's up? Aura Gate stuff again?
I'm not an Aura Gate alarm, you know?
Didn't mean it like that yo. So it's somethin' else then?
That's what I'm trying to find out. But it's definitely Dragon Stream related.
What is it then? Just get to the point already.
To the point then.
Have you ever heard of the "Hero Search Disappearances"?
Hero Search? By hero do you mean something like comic book superheroes?
I've heard of something like that.
They're a series of recent missing persons cases where people have gone missing after saying
"There's a hero who will rescue me" or something along those lines.
Correct! I knew you'd be up to date with this kind of thing.
That's preposterous though, superheroes don't exist in real life.
Of course they do. Like in kung fu, there's...
Umm, gatekeeper? We can talk about that later. Back to topic please.
Oh right. So people have gone missing,
but the good news is I know where they are. Just need to go and check it out.
I see. Aight, gotcha!
Let's go and look for this hero then.
Holy shit...
Well, to state the obvious, it's gone full on Aura Gate.
But... This has never happened to this degree before. It's extraordinary.
Really? It doesn't look any different than the others.
Not in terms of space, but density.
Density? So it's like a overstuffed dumpling?
What kind of analogy is that?
Overstuffed... Hmmm... Not quite like that....
I wonder though, what really is inside there...?
Well, we ain't gonna find out if we stay here. Is entry possible?
Yes, perfectly possible! Just leave it to me.
Aight then. Liberators, time to investigate!
"And how are things on your end?"
Surprisingly normal. I'm kinda baffled.
I don't see any demons around either. Are you sure we're in the right place?
"According to my senses, yes."
...? Hey guys, is that a person over there...?
Yo! You over there!
>Megakin waves his hands wildly to catch the young man's attention.
>The young man suddenly starts dashing at the Liberators in full speed!
W-Whoa! Is that a zombie?! A real zombie?
Yo, don't tell me this place is overstuffed with zombies...
>You all brace yourselves for impact,
>but the young man runs right past you
Aaaargh!
>and takes out the demon trying to blindside you from behind!
...My guess is no.
Whoa, so many demons! Where did THEY come from?!
No time to gawk man! We gotta help that guy!
>The young man stands his ground against the demons.
Food!

NOT good!
Devil...!
>The young man punches the incoming demons awkwardly in the face,
Argh!
Down...
Oof!
load...
Eeek!
>The demons all dissipate.

The way he moves...
It's like he can't fight at all but...
Yeah... What the hell is going on? How can a regular human being...
Whatever man, let's just go thank him.
Yo! Thanks for the assist man, you're a real lifesaver!
I have a few questions I'd like to ask you though, what exactly is this place...

...?
Yo man, you cryin'?
The voices...
Huh?
Those voices again...
Asking me... for help...
>The young man dashes off as suddenly as he came...
He's gone...
We're just going to let him run off? Shouldn't we go after him?
Aight, we gotta catch up with him. Let's go!
